'''Hassan Kadesh Mahboob''' ({{langx|ar|حَسَن كَادِش مَحْبُوب}}, born 26 September 1992) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{cite web |title=HASSAN KADESH |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/hasan-kadesh/255776/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=حسن كادش محبوب - Hassan Kadsh |url=https://www.kooora.com/?player=90310}}</ref>

==Club career==
Kadesh began his career at [[Ettifaq FC|Al-Ettifaq]]. He captained the side from 2015 until his departure in 2017. On 3 July 2017, Kadesh joined [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]] on a four-year contract for a reported fee of [[Saudi riyal|SAR]]6 million.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://m.kooora.com/?n=601228 | title=بالصور: الهلال يضم ثنائي الاتفاق رسميًا| date=9 July 2019}}</ref> On 21 January 2020, Kadesh joined [[Al-Taawoun FC|Al-Taawoun]] on a three-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=التعاون يتعاقد مع حسن كادش | date=20 January 2020 |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=887646}}</ref> On 27 January 2023, Kadesh renewed his contract with Al-Taawoun.<ref>{{cite web |title=رسميًا.. التعاون يُمدد تعاقده مع حسن كادش |date=27 January 2023 |url=https://www.alyaum.com/article/6449232}}</ref> On 31 August 2023, Kadesh joined [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] on a three-year deal for an undisclosed fee reported to be [[Saudi riyal|SAR]]60 million, becoming the most expensive Saudi player in history.<ref>{{cite web |title=الاتحاد يعلن التعاقد مع حسن كادش لمدة 3 مواسم |url=https://www.alriyadh.com/2030283}}</ref>

==International career==
He captained the Saudi Arabia national Under-21 team for two years and then joined the Saudi Arabia Olympic Team.

